<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-638-617  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 638 617.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 15 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Canadian Ogivar Technologies intros 286 laptop. (Internote 286portable computer) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Endrijonas, Janet.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ogivar Technologies (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Ogivar Technologies Internote 286 (Portable computer) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Computer industryProduct IntroductionNotebook Computers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CANADIAN OGIVAR TECHNOLOGIES INTROS 286 LAPTOP MONTREAL, QUEBEC, CANADA, 1990OCT 15 (NB) -- Ogivar Technologies has introduced a light-weight notebookcomputer called the Internote 286.andP;  The system features a VGA-compatible LCDdisplay, a full-size embedded keyboard and a 20 MB hard disk drive.andM;Without the battery, the unit weighs only 4.8 pounds.andP;  The system employs an80C286 microprocessor and has a 12.5 MHz (megahertz) operating speed.andP;  One MB(megabytes) of RAM (random access memory) is standard and isfactory-expandable to 5 MB.andP;  The screen is high-density supertwist 10-inchLCD with 460 x 480 pixel resolution.andP;  There is a video adaptor that is saidto &quot;intelligently convert&quot; colors into 32 shades of grey.andM;The company says that the keyboard has the feel of a desktop computerkeyboard with 82 full size keys and 101-key emulation for programs written touse a full-101 key keyboard.andM;The overall footprint of the unit is less than 1 square foot.andP;  It has aremovable, rechargeable NiCad battery pack that is good for two hours and astandard AC Adaptor/Quick Recharger that plugs into an AC power source.andM;The Internote 286 is available immediately at a list price of $2,999.andM;(Janet Endrijonas/19901015/Press Contact: Al Safarikas, Ogivar Technologies,514-737-3340)</TEXT></DOC>